1. [wsl --install] (powershell or cmd: run as administrator)
2. [wsl --install -d UBUNTU]

#To install Redis on WSL (ie. Ubuntu):

1. Open your WSL terminal (ie. Ubuntu).
2. Update your Ubuntu packages: sudo apt update
3. Once the packages have updated, install Redis with: sudo apt install redis-server

#Start

1.  Open your WSL terminal (ie. Ubuntu) & redis-server
2.  Open another WSL terminal (ie. Ubuntu) & run redis-cli
